{
  "text": "Six of the participants in the study were involved in a collision while driving. Although many factors contribute to an accident, it is noteworthy that two accidents occurred in singletask conditions (1 older adult and 1 younger adult) and four accidents occurred in dual-task conditions (1 older adult and 3 younger adults). Although the low frequency of accidents in this study precludes traditional statistical analysis, this twofold increase is likely to have important consequences for traffic safety (see [CITATION_1] .",
